Even when using statechart, I think that it can be realized by making use of exclusion rules and deleting from redis queue in accordance with exclusion rules when trouble2 comes first.

```py
from durable.lang import *

with statechart('monitor'):
    with state('start'):
        @to('normal')
        def start(c):
            pass

    with state('normal'):
        @to('trouble1_received')
        @when_all(m.subject == 'trouble1')
        def trouble1_action(c):
            print('receive trouble1')

        @to('normal')
        @when_all(m.subject != 'trouble1')
        def reset(c):
            print("--normal--")

    with state('trouble1_received'):
        @to('problem')
        @when_all(m.subject == 'trouble2')
        def trouble2_action(c):
            print('--ALERT--')

    with state('problem'):
        @to('normal')
        def restart(c):
            pass
run_all()
```

